From 1974 to 1992 she worked for newspaper L'Ora, chronicling the hundreds of deaths between rival clans. Her library contained more than 600,000 images, including the shot of a boy with a stocking over his head playing at being a hitman. She later moved into politics as a councillor with the Green Party and worked as a deputy in Sicily's regional assembly. She had three daughters with Franco Stagnitta, but the marriage ended when he fired a shot at her after finding her with a lover. Letizia Battagliaborn March 5 1935, died April 13, 2022, aged 87 